reviews:
[{'author_name': 'Patrick Pedersen', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117854153026658229580/reviews', 'language': 'da', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-xCdIHpC-Qpk/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AB6qoq1xvSLxgau9w65h0KIDzTGWASEGfw/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo/photo.jpg', 'rating': 1, 'relative_time_description': '3 weeks ago', 'text': 'Forfærdelig oplevelse

DVAnlæg har ikke evner til at udføre et anlægsprojekt indenfor aftalt kvalitet eller tid.

I vores tilfælde formåede DVAnlæg at anlægge omkring 250 KVM belægning uden bundsikring (Stabilgrus) selvom de kontaktuelt havde forpligtet sig til det.

De kunne heller ikke finde ud af at planere eller gruppe en græsplæne på omkring 600 KVM.

DVAnlæg måtte lave _hele_ projektet om af 2 omgange og alligevel var der kvalitetsproblemer. DVAnlæg valgte i sende ende at lukke sagen ved betale sig fra det.

Dette har strakt sig over en periode på 2 år, hvilket er ret lang til at vente.

Jeg vil på det kraftigste fraråde folk at benytte denne anlægsgartner, de er utroværdige og har simpelthen ikke kompetencerne til at udføre det arbejde som de ellers har forpligtet sig selv til.', 'time': 1526065333}, {'author_name': 'BS chen', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105163272934947056043/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-lzYPzyTda-U/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AB6qoq3JDJFhrLAiTDN564MHRlXiBnXp_Q/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba8/photo.jpg', 'rating': 3, 'relative_time_description': '9 months ago', 'text': '', 'time': 1503501345}]

reviews: [{'author_name': 'Anders Grabow', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111908148013870907713/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-aTfeO8hMe7w/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAmM/_3GOMbqwF7I/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4/photo.jpg', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': 'a month ago', 'text': 'Would have given this beautiful park five stars for the location, the view of the royal families old summerhouse (that will make almost every other summerhouse look like an outhouse) and the magnificent trees and flowers. But. When the sun is out it becomes a place to party / and forget to pick up your trash. \nThank god the local government are very good at cleaning up after the parties.', 'time': 1524388642}, {'author_name': 'Louise Friis Jensen', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105090836471009204222/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-awqVquuOZaI/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AB6qoq3Bxr2_XDYsrGagSYYj7UZTqxRGiA/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'in the last week', 'text': "One of my favourite spots to hang out when the sun is out. There is always people there. You can bring food and drinks and make a picnic. And as a bonus there are public toilets so you don't have to worry about that. It isn't a park I would visit for beauty, but to hang out in. You can however see Rosenborg castle and that's nice :)", 'time': 1527667643}, {'author_name': 'Brian Smales', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113027227414037590078/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-0m_YvMh8iLM/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAACw/TH6tg6cgB6o/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '2 weeks ago', 'text': 'This is a well kept park and is frequented by locals, particularly on sunny days so they can strip down and enjoy some sun on skin. There are many open grassed areas for picnics etc. Various forms of skittles are played by groups of friends.  There is an enclosed sand pit and play area for children. Lovely flower gardens are spread throughout the Garden.', 'time': 1526510854}, {'author_name': 'Bettina zens', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112038273970425198825/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-cg1-dKJWghs/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AB6qoq1WpfQxcwmK1PWCZdCS7SGBWVC6Hw/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '2 weeks ago', 'text': "Doubtlessly one of the must-sees when in Copenhagen. The gardens surround the Rosenborg castle, which in itself is already worth a visit. The gardens are very big (I think as big as the Botanical Gardens) and feature grass to lie on on a nice summer day, trees that offer shadow, benches to sit on, and different parts of the garden are styled differently - there is a rose garden, then there's the little labyrinth, etc. It is very nice to come here for taking a walk, enjoying the good weather for a bit or just relaxing on the grass - and also for taking pictures of the pretty castle and the gardens, of course!", 'time': 1526549436}, {'author_name': 'Jonas monas', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111401822493218814238/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-PpwOqtsXBqM/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAACM/HLUP2beV2DQ/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '3 weeks ago', 'text': "A wonderful and lovely garden within the city centre of Copenhagen. There is no entry fee to enter it inside the garden are lots of benches to sit and it's allowed to relax on the  grass as well. Right next to the garden is the Rosenborg which you can enter from outside for free as well. I would recommend doing that.", 'time': 1526038017}]

Excellent museum overall.", 'time': 1516300976}, {'author_name': 'Henrik Røn', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108771690398272832703/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-sypYUbRpQTg/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAA-4/JoJrRMnnsnY/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4/photo.jpg', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': '7 months ago', 'text': 'We went 3 adults and two kinds aged 10 and 12. The kids and I did a special autumn holiday activity tour and they enjoyed it, especially that some activities were hands-on, e.g. taking and reading fingerprints and wearing policeuniforms. The parents saw the permanent exhibition and said it was very interesting.', 'time': 1508437780}, {'author_name': 'tommy burke', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110005575365861390749/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-mxbtA_g3LSI/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAU4/LL2nnBXl5rg/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo/photo.jpg', 'rating': 1, 'relative_time_description': 'a month ago', 'text': 'I hate cops,\nbut I like the gear', 'time': 1524915918}, {'author_name': 'Lee Cherry', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109530340715657378099/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-msFMJKW9Saw/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAACk/NJ8b6Z6SeiE/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': "You could easily miss this attraction in Copenhagen, because it receives little publicity - we only found out about it because it is located near our accommodation, which was a 15 - 20 minute walk from the CBD. Our visit to this museum turned out to be one of the highlights of our stay in Copenhagen. The museum is located in an old Police Station, which significantly, was once the centre of police action in response to a major riot that happened nearby a few decades ago. However, the museum doesn't just present a history of the police force in Denmark. It also deals with the administration of justice, including crime and punishment. It was interesting to see how then crimes such as prostitution and pornography were dealt with in the past, as well as how basic the forensic techniques were 100 years or more ago. There are interesting displays of police regalia, equipment, those early forensic techniques and of course, police cells. While the text of the descriptions on the displays is in Danish, there are a number of English language guides that are provided at reception, for loan, free of charge. Unfortunately, the English language guides do not include all of the items on display, but because the displays are so visual, the lack of English text is not a problem. The Museum is operated by volunteer staff, mostly former police officers from what we could determine. This means that the opening hours are limited, so you should check online first to establish when the museum is open. All in all, this was a very interesting place to visit.", 'time': 1467579438}]

Got a visit to a weeds filled discolored and deserted storage area. ', 'time': 1478815837}, {'author_name': 'Wang Tiger', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109122889060416093791/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-0m0mFaNruZs/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AB6qoq1rCwGdXD7y59pirx8KZdOFKhj1pg/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '2 years ago', 'text': "This is a project by JDS Architects + BIG - Bjarke Ingels Group and it is located at Sundby Harbour, Copenhagen, Denmark. It was submitted to Architecture News Plus (ANP) by JDS Architects. Project's program: Sailing club and youth house with play area. There are fourteen images for Maritime Youth House.

The concept of the project is that instead of using 1/4 of the project's budget, originally allocated by the client to cleaning the polluted soil of the site, we discovered that the pollution was heavy metals and therefore stable. So if you didn't reach the ground you wouldn't have to remove/clean it... we then decided to lay out a wooden deck on the entirety of the site. Thus spending money for architecture/program/effect rather than invisible waste.

Two clients had to share the facilities: a sail club and a youth house. Their desires were opposite: the youth house wanted outdoor space for the kids to play, the sail club needed most of the site to park their boats... the building is the literal results of our negotiations with these 2 contradictory demands: when the deck bubbles up it allows for boat storage underneath, still letting the kids run/play above...

The interior of the building is very basic, with one major characteristic: the front house, which is used as common room and where most of the daily activities take place, is more luxurious than the workshop and storage building on the back corner, but still in a very puritan way. The difference is that the floor in the workshop is a standard grey concrete while in the community space it’s a white concrete with white stones. The presence of hard surfaces everywhere on the inside is meant as a contrast to the wooden exterior, almost like an inversion of what is commonly done (wood indoor, asphalt outdoor). This is reflecting the dominance of outdoor activities of the youth house. The actual ‘room’ of the Maritime Youth house IS the wooden deck… it englobes all the programs, indoor and outdoor.", 'time': 1455965717}, {'author_name': 'Péter Kosik', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100683257759223934048/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-1droeaDHOdM/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAF0/8H1r1dfOrio/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'Inspirational BIG architecture, first of its kind. Pure feelings.', 'time': 1468610141}, {'author_name': 'Szilárd Veisz', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102613714032911095502/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-A6MzqGdPVVM/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAADtA/yagBElvjVMI/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'Great architecture, nice viewing point to the see.', 'time': 1469097996}]

[{'author_name': 'Lee Cherry', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109530340715657378099/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-msFMJKW9Saw/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAACk/NJ8b6Z6SeiE/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'Immaculate apartment with original furnishings from a wealthy Danish family dating back to 1890. 

Two sisters lived there until their deaths and donated their apartment to the National museum. As they were unmarried, nothing in the apartment was updated after their father passed away in 1890. They were one of the first houses in Denmark to get electricity and running water. They even had one of the first telephones; family had 1 digit phone number - 7 - showing their prominence in the country. 

Everything is preserved perfectly and allows for a glimpse into how life was lived over 100 years ago. 

Available as a guided tour only, as apartment is protected by the state. 

Guided tour is free with Copenhagen card from National Museum. Can redeem in lieu of free gift.', 'time': 1467582135}, {'author_name': 'Dan Thorup', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101492900481009760313/reviews', 'language': 'da', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-Sa5_8_65sBA/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAK48/GBxVfnny5pc/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a month ago', 'text': 'Utrolig historisk og spændende oplevelse. reviews:
[{'author_name': 'Patrick G', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111390515130794379577/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-3Mvre0ot_3g/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AB6qoq2Fifb6hzK8EiHgMk47OUrTqx44LA/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '3 weeks ago', 'text': "Tivoli is great. [{'author_name': 'Ulla Paarmann', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113962546054226427810/reviews', 'language': 'da', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-jeOmlnJBylE/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AB6qoq0A1z388YRXtr-ZtMb6eJ7GEGZL_A/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo/photo.jpg', 'rating': 2, 'relative_time_description': '5 years ago', 'text': '2 gange tidligere har jeg benyttet - og anbefalet naboer m.fl. dette firma p.g.a. Henning Lysholms velvilje og villighed til at påtage sig ekstra opgaver uden beregning, så da jeg denne gang fik et tilbud på lægning af fliser på terrasse og havegang, accepterede jeg det derfor uden tøven.
Men desværre er jeg blevet skuffet  - og vred fordi jeg føler mig gjort stærkt til grin:
Da terrassen var færdig og havegangen halvt færdig, sagde Henning Lysholm at der skulle lægges jord uden om fliserne for at de ikke skulle skride. På mit spørgsmål om det ikke var noget han gjorde, svarede han at det ikke var med i tilbuddet. (Dette var nu slet ikke udspecificeret). Men han ville vise mig hvordan jeg selv skulle gøre det.
På cykel med anhænger skaffede jeg så 400 l sphagnum, hvad der morgenen efter viste sig at være forkert. Nye cykelture for at bytte til blomsterjord der også viste sig at indeholde sphagniúm. Da jeg spurgte ham om hvor jeg så skulle skaffe jord fra, vidste han det ikke, og heller ikke hvor meget der skulle bruges.
Flinke naboer kørte mig så til planteskolen for at købe den rigtige jord til en pris af over 300 kr.
Efter min mening burde det som en selvfølge være med i tilbuddet - eller stå der at det ikke var - i stedet for at man sender en gammel kone på 75  + ud på strabadserende cykelture.
Heldigvis var Henning Lysholm villig til at lægge jorden ud, da jeg havde skaffet den.

It has a wonderful interactive tablet set up and so many glorious and informative displays!', 'time': 1498501397}, {'author_name': 'Lee Cherry', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109530340715657378099/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-msFMJKW9Saw/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAACk/NJ8b6Z6SeiE/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': "I first visited this museum at its old home around 9 years ago and have wanted to go back ever since.
It's new home is a bit clinical compared to its last but it is still well worth a visit. Some of the instruments are amazing - mind boggling, I mean who on earth designed them?? Or even first thought of the concepts?

The man on the desk was extremely helpful, giving us the tablets with the English translations for all the exhibits, and more information about the actual museum.

The only thing I cannot understand about this place - why is it so quiet? A museum such as this should be be full, busy, but it is so quiet - we were there a couple of hours and no-one else came in (also saw a similar note in their visitor book).

If you fancy a fascinating option of what to do in Copenhagen, here it is!", 'time': 1467583944}]

reviews:
[{'author_name': 'Vincenzo Reale', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114002978433768977734/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-7vv-582yIUU/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAABcQ/azbxaApCZ-4/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '3 months ago', 'text': 'Nicely arranged museum within a beautiful historical building. The part at ground floor on prehistory up to Vickings is really thoughtfully arranged with plentiful of artifacts shown in a compelling way. The part on colonialism is nice but I felt it was a bit too small, while the anthropological section is a great display if objects from all over the world. I found that the part on Danish history is a bit too crowded to be experienced, a smaller selection of objects arranged in a neater way would probably be more effective. Also the medieval and renaissance section would benefit a re-arrangement. Anyway it is a great museum to visit and interesting also for kids.', 'time': 1518464274}, {'author_name': 'Radosław Genew', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111281787331934660976/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-aI3YpNFaIPA/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AB6qoq2b-edyg2o67ODfYnErPWnk__Cnwg/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3/photo.jpg', 'rating': 3, 'relative_time_description': '3 weeks ago', 'text': "The room quality standard does not justify the high price but maybe the location does.
Not having any doors between the toilet and the rest of the room is not my preference of aroma-therapy.

En mindre permanent samling med bl.a. Th Philipsen malerier fra Kastrup og omegn er ganske fin. Dertil skiftende udstillinger af varierende kvalitet, men generelt god, af enten samtids- eller nyere kunst. 

Efter en gennemgribende renovering og udbygning i 2013-14 blev der mere plads, inkl en udvidelse af cafeen der som så mange andre museumscafeer er mere rolig og fjernt fra verdens vrimmel ... hvis man ellers er til det.

Free with the Copenhagen card!', 'time': 1527271023}, {'author_name': 'Aslı Özcivelek', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110401894962418935624/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-GkxUxdDefEE/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAADY/GqRP5YHa6QM/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4/photo.jpg', 'rating': 3, 'relative_time_description': '3 weeks ago', 'text': "Denmark is really well known for its design and I have studied it in all of my classes so I was very excited to visit this museum. It had so many chairs which are all super iconic design artifacts. The way they displayed those and the design of the information cards was amazing. I expected the rest of the museum to be like that room as well. I still would recommend visiting it for sure. It also has a pretty cute garden and a cafe. The staff was super friendly. reviews:
[{'author_name': 'Michał Drwal', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104449457365371382653/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-hkEgrkjYy1s/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAM9w/sw1tFxva3Bc/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '3 weeks ago', 'text': 'A tiny palace in the middle of a park that holds the old and rare (and sometimes quirky) objects of the Royal Family. 

Four stories, a basement and a treasury are packed. Interesting snapshot of "living large" 400 years past (the royals have not lived in the palace since 17th century and they used it as storage). You can see casks with 300 years old wine, crowns and jewels in the treasury, a whole room dedicated to summer holiday memorabilia from Venice.

Give it a 1.5 hours, which is enough time and then picnic in the park or go to the Botanical Gardens.

Due to the limited space can get crowded quite easily. As everywhere in Copenhagen - the service is impeccable and the staff very friendly and helpful.', 'time': 1525846255}, {'author_name': 'Shaun Maloney', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110951289022648499143/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-c20go50R_Ko/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AB6qoq3-_dCORKHzSI2XUlfy4OLnQlBttQ/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '2 months ago', 'text': "Amazing castle. More modern than most I've visited though. Amazing artworks and statues. The throne room is a must see obviously. The crown jewels are then in the basement. Me and my friend debated whether they were the real ones or not, but we'll never really know. Handy maps in many languages available so easy to see where you are. The grounds are also stunning.", 'time': 1522596528}, {'author_name': 'Satish Chandran', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111757298443404873095/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-kFBCxN84b0U/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAADzA/pmkU_I4jBlo/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '3 weeks ago', 'text': "Beautiful castle with interesting stories attached to it, most notably that of the trouser wetting chair, the King's toilet etc. The Great Hall is impressive. This 400 year old castle is a good place to visit. Entry fee applicable. Close to the town centre. Free entry with the Copenhagen card. Highly recommended.", 'time': 1526160284}, {'author_name': 'Nicole Wickenheiser', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114334394703089267909/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-_ZYR3tzkrVw/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AB6qoq00XdEismgnETqze7hFu09ikYx-rg/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a month ago', 'text': 'Such a beauty if a castle! 
Visiting here was easy access using city transit making the venture out within young family very fun. Upon entering the grounds we were in love with the building. Once we’d walked inside and even our young ones were able to Appreciate the history the castle had to shared. We loved every second, but most of all viewing the crown jewels. It’s a sight for every wanna bebpeoness!', 'time': 1523481589}, {'author_name': 'David Morfin', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102392465667820048603/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-0CPYj60kyXg/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAHU/jbh2coold2g/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2/photo.jpg', 'rating': 1, 'relative_time_description': '4 weeks ago', 'text': 'Very disappointing. If you're going to Copenhagen for the first time, I would recommend checking this out first, because the crown jewels are impressive, but everything else pales miserably compared with every other museum and castle I visited. The rooms were dim, dirty, and dust covered. Many of the items were damaged and didn't appear to have ever been cleaned or restored. The information "app" was really just a web page, the only way to get to it after signing on to their captive portal was to scan one of the few QR codes on a handful of the displays, and navigation was difficult when when the items were cataloged (when they weren't there was no way to get more information, unless maybe you'd paid for their guidebook). The guards all looked like they wished they could be anywhere but there. The jewels in the basement were impressive, and the grounds were lovely, but the interior upper floors just felt shabby. Christianborg Castle was much cleaner and more beautiful, and the museums like the David's Collection were much more informative.', 'time': 1525612299}]

reviews:
[{'author_name': 'Michał Drwal', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104449457365371382653/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-hkEgrkjYy1s/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAM9w/sw1tFxva3Bc/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5/photo.jpg', 'rating': 2, 'relative_time_description': '3 weeks ago', 'text': 'Architecture (being a huge selling point) looks underwhelming. Designed in a way that allows for "modern look" photographs for architecture blogs does not wow a visitor.

Interior is crammed. Some of the tanks are clearly too small for its occupants.

We did not understand why over one of the tanks there is a small open space where a number of birds living on cliffs (apparently including puffins) are kept with no room to fly.

Controversial "piece" is a pool where visitors can touch various species of sea fauna. We declined over the doubts if this serves the animals.

Most of the tanks and the aquarium gives a depressing feeling to animal lovers.

The shop is packed with usual wares of plastic toys with little consideration for the damages plastic waste causes to the sea life.

The highlight of the place are two sea otters that have a (well deserved) star status. They have a decently sized enclosure and seem happy, with dedicated caretakers. Even outside the feeding hours the otters provide a great spectacle.', 'time': 1525786528}, {'author_name': 'M KA', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116431743825036073742/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-IhtmXrmYglI/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AB6qoq0aq1kEE8i9cTrBtR5BCnb4eUzMBA/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '2 weeks ago', 'text': "A beautiful and highly recommended place to visit if you like sea life, the facility itself is built is a very interesting way that allows you to comfortably and easily go through all of their aquariums and displays. There's a variety of different interesting sea life animals spread across well built exhibitions, informative and interesting.
Very easy to get to as it is right next to the airport and has plenty of public transportation options.", 'time': 1526563123}, {'author_name': 'Pınar Akyurek', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101634436368148613190/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-LgCRqH0gQ3k/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAGzw/5J-If4l6X9c/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2/photo.jpg', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': '3 weeks ago', 'text': "It wasn't as big as some of the others but it sure is nice inside. The architecture of the building is pretty and once you are inside you have a lot of activities for kids to do. I really enjoyed watching the shark and otter feedings. The only thing is the entrance fee is a little high but in my opinion, totally worth it. I even got a stuffed toy for myself! 😆", 'time': 1526200194}, {'author_name': 'Max Ernst', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106649055331143424724/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-6PWV-1PS_vM/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AB6qoq0JcROMHEXDlw8W4YPh2kH8_xZPtg/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a week ago', 'text': "Best aquarium I've ever visited. From sea otters ( only watch them if you are prepared to never find anything else remotely cute), to hammerhead sharks, from octopus to a hole shoal of herring. This is the place to go for an Incredible underwater experience.", 'time': 1527059551}, {'author_name': 'Emanuele Torres', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106803455294107369617/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-Y7Kyc6YC2fw/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAADk/FwcHY29qUug/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '2 weeks ago', 'text': 'The Aquarium is very well designed, all the tanks are clean and the fish are healthy. 
The otters are particularly cute. They feed the shark, otter and coral reef tanks during the day and do some explanation in Danish, English and German.
There is a lovely terrace with a restaurant and the view on the Sound.', 'time': 1526844384}]

reviews: [{'author_name': 'Sebastian Mohr', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110807244625732105290/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-7VBDOtmsXHY/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAyk/-xfCCYvr7Mo/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5/photo.jpg', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'If you manage to get onto the roof of this building you have a beautiful view of the botanical garden itself and a large part of Copenhagen', 'time': 1496383399}, {'author_name': 'Pascal RIDE', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114369873348463662036/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-8IfFSnfDM1Q/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAB4Y/0BMJhcsjvrI/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'worth to visit', 'time': 1467544861}, {'author_name': 'André Cella', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/118312489149430695361/reviews', 'language': 'pt', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-flXQez5SjlM/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAMx0/F4YebSobZcg/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba7/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a week ago', 'text': 'O jardim botânico foi um passeiozinho despretensioso que, na minha opinião, valeu a pena. Os caras conseguiram reunir plantas de literalmente todas as partes do mundo. Há alguns morrinhos pelos quais passam umas trilhas e, à medida que se caminha, vai-se vendo as plaquinhas com o nome e a origem de cada planta. Existem também alguns lagos, com plantas aquáticas, inclusive vitórias-régias amazônicas.  No centro de tudo, uma grande estufa subdividida em micro-climas, para possibilitar a sobrevivência de plantas que não crescem ao ar livre no clima dinamarquês. A parte tropical devia estar, com certeza, com mais de 35°C!', 'time': 1527165950}, {'author_name': 'Christian Nygaard', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106315560518701134482/reviews', 'language': 'da', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-JDldmX8aXfY/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAABU/BJJqRUhdAkc/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4/photo.jpg', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': '10 months ago', 'text': 'Virkelig en joke i sig selv.', 'time': 1500586970}, {'author_name': 'Dávid Bartoš', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106882234772763845464/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-j9fEgBj5-R4/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAzQ/GSQDtFzbCe0/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4/photo.jpg', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': '', 'time': 1488730533}]

Lovely building and space too. We went round the French art ~1800-1950, spread over three floors. The collection is remarkable, with all the big names (Monet, Degas, Renoir, Gaugain, Renoir, and even some Rousseau that were remarkably different from the 'primitive' paintings he is famous for). First room had some of the more modern artists (Miro, Man Ray), but most of it was older than that (a dozen or so other rooms).\n\nIt was a little frustrating not to have an audio guide or even labels with comments by the paintings.
